certain versionz of Linux (kernel) limit tha set of SCSI commandz allowed for
non-root users. Even if usage without root identitizzle is possible up in nuff cases,
some thang drivers still may fail, show unexplainable problems n' generally
the problems become harder ta debug. Da risk fo' buffer-underruns be also
increased. Y'all KNOW dat shit, muthafucka! See the
.IR "PROCESS SCHEDULING PRIORITY"
section below fo' mo' details.
