As a rule of thumb, tha FIFO size should be at least equal ta tha size
of tha internal buffer of tha CD/DVD-Recorder n' no mo' than half of
the physical amount of RAM available up in tha machine.
If tha FIFO size is big-ass enough, tha FIFO statistics will print a FIFO
empty count of zero n' tha FIFO min fill aint below 20%.
It aint wise ta use too much space fo' tha FIFO. If you need more
than 8 MB ta write a CD at a speed less than 20x from a image on a
local file system on a idle machine, yo' machine is either underpowered,
has hardware problems or is mis-configured.
If you like ta write DVDs or CDs at higher speed, it make sense
to use at least 16\ MB fo' tha FIFO.
.sp
On oldschool n' lil' small-ass machines, you need ta be mo' careful wit tha FIFO size.
