.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
For all examplez below, it is ghon be assumed dat tha CD/DVD-Recorder is
connected ta tha primary SCSI buz of tha machine. Da SCSI target id is
set ta 2.
.PP
To record a pure CD-ROM at double speed, rockin data from tha file
.IR cdimage.raw :
.PP
    wodim \-v speed=2 dev=2,0 cdimage.raw
.PP
To create a image fo' a ISO 9660 filesystem wit Rock Ridge extensions:
.PP
    genisoimage \-R \-o cdimage.raw /home/joerg/master/tree
.PP
To check tha resultin file before freestylin ta CD on Solaris:
.PP
    mount \-r \-F fbk \-o type=hsfs /dev/fbk0:cdimage.raw /mnt
.PP
On Linux:
.PP
    mount cdimage.raw \-r \-t iso9660 \-o loop /mnt
.PP
Go on with:
.br
    ls \-lR /mnt
.br
    umount /mnt
.PP
If tha overall speed of tha system is sufficient n' tha structure of
the filesystem aint too complex, wodim will run without bustin an
image of tha ISO 9660 filesystem. Right back up in yo muthafuckin ass. Simply run tha pipeline:
.PP
    genisoimage \-R /master/tree | wodim \-v fs=6m speed=2 dev=2,0 -
.PP
Da recommended minimum FIFO size fo' hustlin dis pipeline is 4 MBytes.
As tha default FIFO size is 4 MB, tha 
.B fs=
option needz only be present if you wanna bust a gangbangin' finger-lickin' different FIFO size.
If yo' system is loaded, you should run genisoimage up in tha real time class like a muthafucka.
To raise tha prioritizzle of 
.B genisoimage
replace tha command
.PP
    genisoimage \-R /master/tree
.br
by
.br
    priocntl \-e \-c RT \-p 59 genisoimage \-R /master/tree
.sp
on Solaris n' by
.sp
    sick --18 genisoimage \-R /master/tree
.sp
on systems dat don't have
.B "UNIX International
compliant real-time scheduling.
.PP
wodim runs at prioritizzle 59 on Solaris, you should run genisoimage
at no mo' than prioritizzle 58. On other systems, you should run genisoimage
at no less than sick --18.
.PP
Creatin a CD-ROM without file system image on disk has been tested
on a Sparcstation-2 wit a Yamaha CDR-400. Well shiiiit, it did work up ta quad speed
when tha machine was not loaded.
A fasta machine may be able ta handle quad speed also up in tha loaded case.
.PP
To record a pure CD-DA (audio) at single speed, wit each track contained
in a gangbangin' file named
.IR track01.cdaudio ,
.IR track02.cdaudio ,
etc:
.PP
    wodim \-v speed=1 dev=/dev/cdrw -audio track*.cdaudio
.PP
To check if it is ghon be aiiight ta use double speed fo' tha example above. 
Use tha dummy write option:
.PP
